<p>A U.N. fact-finding commission reported on October 27 that Russian forces used small drones to target ordinary people near the front line in Kherson, dropping hand grenades and recording attacks, conduct the panel said may amount to a war crime . The inquiry describes drones following people into shelters and hounding residents out of their homes, a pattern documented by interviews, video and field evidence collected by investigators . The release of the report has intensified calls for accountability and highlighted urgent protection needs for civilians living close to active fighting .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/ipXnAp32N-P8DiJYEENeR_nobxsQ9nJrW198fse71Y3dliyCLtoWa7Wl4IwSiyKMWLegr1vcPTkZr1V_MkgGEsbNo5y026E7XQDwmTkEc1Zk0rdqpyWzpSiMJfPG6Dso9Uuz22fKXYkg2sy9_tABMGW5pA55-RfpOQW2C5GZVZcs6hGZI6QcnDwqwbB-c-sNis_YhqgYcMH_AxqFVEFnuXZf' alt='Taking cover near the scene of shelling as a drone flew overhead in Kherson, Ukraine, in 2023.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Scale of displacement: Investigators say the drone campaign has driven thousands of people to abandon whole frontline areas, producing concentrated local displacement in the Kherson region .</li><li>Pursuit tactics: The report documents drones not only striking but tracking and filming individuals as they sought shelter, a practice used repeatedly to push residents from their homes .</li><li>Weapon modification: Field evidence described in the inquiry shows hand grenades routinely adapted for release from small commercial drones, a method observed in multiple incidents in Kherson .</li><li>Legal framing: Beyond labeling some attacks as war crimes, the commission concluded that the pattern of deliberate, systematic attacks against civilians can amount to a crime against humanity, urging further legal scrutiny and accountability measures .</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>U.N. fact-finding commission: The commission reported that small drones routinely targeted ordinary people by dropping hand grenades and recording the attacks, a pattern that may amount to a war crime. (<a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/27/world/europe/russia-drones-target-civilians.html'>The New York Times</a>)</li><li>Ukrainian officials: Authorities said drones chased civilians from frontline settlements and that people have been forced to flee entire areas because of the hounding attacks. (<a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/russian-drones-hunt-down-chase-out-ukrainian-civilians-un-inquiry-finds-9527322#publisher=newsstand'>NDTV</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/27/world/europe/russia-drones-target-civilians.html'>Russia Aims Drone Attacks at Civilians, a War Crime, U.N. Inquiry Says</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/russian-drones-hunt-down-chase-out-civilians-in-ukraine-un-inquiry-finds'>Russian drones hunt down, chase out civilians in Ukraine, UN inquiry finds</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.rferl.org/a/ukraine-russia-war-united-nations-report-war-crimes-humanity/33572425.html'>UN Commission Accuses Russia Of New Crime Against Humanity In Ukraine</a> - rferl.org</li><li><a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/russian-drones-hunt-down-chase-out-ukrainian-civilians-un-inquiry-finds-9527322#publisher=newsstand'>Russian drones hunt down, chase out Ukrainian civilians, UN inquiry finds</a> - ndtv.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/russian-drones-hunt-down-chase-out-ukrainian-civilians-un-inquiry-finds'>Russian drones hunt down, chase out Ukrainian civilians, U.N. inquiry finds</a> - japantoday.com</li></ul>